news.title: HDFC invokes 50 lakh pledged shares of Ansal Housing for recovery of dues
news.para: Ansal Housing is engaged in the business of construction and development of residential townships and commercial complexes.

news.title: Gujarat: Wrong plots auctioned after revenue department's blunder
news.para: The Gujarat high court has not only ordered the land to be restored to the neighbouring village, but also directed the revenue department and Timbdi village panchayat to reallot the residential plots to 76 villagers on another land belonging to Timbdi village.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco gets Rs 865 crore from auction of three Ghansoli plots
news.para: The biggest plot (residential-plus-commercial) of over 16,000 sq m was bagged by Satyam Realty for Rs 1.78 lakh per sq m.

news.title: Goa goverment forms SIT to probe land grab cases
news.para: The seven-member SIT is headed by SP (crime branch) Nidhin Valsan, and includes South Goa deputy collector Snehal Prabhu, dySP Braz Menezes, PI Satish Gaude, PI (IRBn) Nilesh Shirodakar, a representative of the department of archaeology, and a representative of the state registrar.

news.title: K Raheja Corp promoters buy JK Lakshmi promoter family's villa in Mumbai for Rs 265 crore
news.para: Kamala Cottage has carpet area of nearly 8,000 sq ft across ground plus one storey structure on the land parcel. The property is freehold and there are no restrictions of any nature on sale, transfer or usage on the same. Both promoters of K Raheja Corp have together paid stamp duty of Rs 15.90 crore for the property’s registration.

news.title: Delhi Development Authority razes cluster near Qutub Minar, residents cry foul
news.para: However, the residents alleged that they had lived in the area for more than 20 years and were not even served evacuation notices. The residents also claimed that they were just verbally warned on Tuesday night.

news.title: Ludhiana: Illegal colonies hit NOC wall, to be marked for future alert
news.para: The municipal commissioner now has the power to issue these NOCs, while the MC is also charged with doing a clear demarcation of authorised and unauthorised colonies for the convenience of future investors.

news.title: Navy working to reduce delay in NOCs for buildings around Goa international airport
news.para: ​Flag Officer Commanding Goa Area (FOGA) Rear Admiral Vikram Menon said that the issue has been discussed with the higher authorities to try and remove the bottlenecks.

news.title: Ghaziabad master plan to be finalised soon, file objections by June 22
news.para: ​So far, GDA has received over 50 objections to its draft from the public, including residents and organisations. June 22 is the last date to file the objections.

news.title: Delhi Development Authority looks to put MPD 2041 on fast track
news.para: In April, a DDA advisory council, headed by the then LG Anil Baijal, reviewed the draft MPD 2041, which incorporates the objections and suggestions from the public. DDA had received approximately 33,000 objections and suggestions in around two and a half months.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders forensic audit of Mahira Group's five affordable housing projects
news.para: According to a DTCP order, the developer fabricated bank guarantees and forged signatures of bank officials on the documents submitted to the department for procuring the licences of its affordable housing projects.

news.title: Gurugram: Takeover of seven private colonies complete, two more likely today
news.para: While the developers of Sushant Lok-2 and 3, Malibu Towne, Vipul World, Rosewood City, Uppal Southend and Ardee City have handed them over to the corporation, the takeover of Greenwood City and Mayfield Garden is still pending.

news.title: SBI hikes minimum interest rate on home loans to 7.55%
news.para: The lender has hiked its External Benchmark-based Lending Rate (EBLR) to a minimum of 7.55 per cent effective today as compared to 7.05 per cent earlier, as per the bank's website.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh waives stamp duty if property transferred to 'family member'
news.para: Minister for stamps and registration Ravindra Jaiswal said that the earlier stamp duty was creating unnecessary tension within families as the high court of registration was now allowing them to settle property issues while the owner was alive.

news.title: IBBI amends rules for swifter redressal of grievances filed against insolvency professionals
news.para: ​IBBI has amended the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India (Grievance and Complaint Handling Procedure) Regulations, 2017 and the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India (Inspection and Investigation) Regulations, 2017, according to an official release on Wednesday.
